decision_conditions: The development permitted shall be begun before the expiration of three years from the date of the original permission (203084FUL).
Reason: In order to comply with the provisions of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 (as amended).

| The development hereby approved shall be carried out in accordance with drawing / document title number(s): A-03-001 Existing Site Plan, ETF-COL-XX-00-DR-A-04-001 P5 Proposed Site Plan, ETF-COL-XX-XX-DR-A-04-101 P3 Square of Wickets Relocation, ETF-COL-XX-XX-DR-A-04-102 P2 External Football Pitches, ETF-COL-XX-GF-DR-A-05-101 P2 Cricket Pavilion Link Garden, ETF-COL-XX-00-DR-A-05-102 P1 Proposed 3G Pitch Line Markings, ETF-COL-XX-XX-DR-A-05-001_S0-P12 General Arrangement Plan, ETF-COL-XX-XX-DR-A-05-002 P3 Roof General Arrangement Plan, ETF-COL-XX-ZZ-DR-A-06-001_S0-P07 General Arrangement Elevations, ETF-COL-XX-ZZ-DR-A-07-001 P1 Proposed GA Sections, ETF-XX-XX-DR-A-13-001 P3 External Works Plan, 220/002/003 P3 Proposed Foul and Surface Water Drainage Layout, 2483(63)E01 P2 Proposed Security Layout prepared by Beech Jackson Partnership dated July 2020, 2483(63)E03 P1 Proposed External Lighting Layout prepared by Beech Jackson Partnership dated July 2020, DWG01 3D Visualisation 1, DWG02 3D Visualisation 2, DWG03 3D Visualisation 3, DWG04 3D Visualisation 4, Acoustic Criterial Memorandum prepared by GL Hearn dated 1 July 2020, Arboricultural Impact Assessment prepared by Meerwood dated May 2020, Arboricultural Survey prepared by Meerwood dated 04.06.2020, BREEAM and Light Pollution Compliance Summary prepared by Whitecroft Lighting dated 08.10.2020, BRUKL Output Document prepared by HM Government dated 18 September 2020, Construction Management Plan prepared by Collinson Construction dated 16 July 2020, Design & Access Statement prepared by Collinson 16 July 2020, Flood Risk Assessment prepared by Waterman dated July 2020, Kolo Bollard prepared by Whitecroft Lighting, Landscape and Ecological Management Plan prepared by Fure.

Reason: For the avoidance of doubt, and in the interests of proper planning. | The external materials to be used in the development shall be as described on the plans and in section 7 of the submitted application form.

Reason: To ensure that the materials harmonise with the surrounding, in accordance with policies 7.4 and 7B of the Ealing Development Management Development Plan 2013, and policies D3 and D4 of the London Plan (2021). | The development shall contain sound reduction index, Rw, for the building envelope in accordance with to the standards of the Council's SPG10 and noise limits specified by BS8233:2014 at the nearest and most affected noise sensitive premises incl. private external amenity spaces and shall be implemented before the development is commenced and retained permanently thereafter.

Reason: To ensure that the amenity of occupiers of the development site/ surrounding premises is not adversely affected by noise, in accordance with Policies 1.1 and 1.2 of the Ealing Development (Core) Strategy (2012), policies 7A & 7B of the Ealing Development Management Development Plan Document (2013), policy D14 of the London Plan (2021), Ealing SPG10 and the National Planning Policy Framework (2021). | The development's external rating noise level emitted from plant/machinery/equipment/ducting/air in- and outlets/ mechanical installations at the development shall ensure that the external rating noise level LAeq emitted will be lower than the lowest existing background sound level LA90 by 10dBA at the most noise sensitive receiver locations at the development site and in surrounding premises. A post installation sound assessment shall be carried out where required to confirm compliance with the noise criteria and additional steps to mitigate noise shall be taken, as necessary.  Approved details shall be implemented prior to occupation/ use of plant/ machinery/ equipment and thereafter be permanently retained.

Reason:   To ensure that the amenity of occupiers of the development site/ surrounding premises is not adversely affected by noise from mechanical installations/ equipment, in accordance with Policies 1.1(j) of the Ealing Core Strategy (2012), policy 7A of the Ealing Development Management Development Plan Document (2013), policies and D14 of the London Plan (2021), the National Planning Policy Framework (2021) and Interim guidance SPG 10 'Noise and Vibration'. | Prior to use, machinery, plant or equipment/ extraction/ ventilation system and ducting at the development shall be mounted with proprietary anti-vibration isolators and fan motors shall be vibration isolated from the casing and adequately silenced and maintained as such.

Reason:   To ensure that the amenity of occupiers of the development site/ surrounding premises is not adversely affected by noise from mechanical installations/ equipment, in accordance with Policies 1.1(j) of the Ealing Core Strategy (2012), policy 7A of the Ealing Development Management Development Plan Document (2013), policy D14 of the London Plan (2021), the National Planning Policy Framework (2021) and Interim guidance SPG 10 'Noise and Vibration'. | The development shall implement prior to occupation/use of the indoor cricket facility, and permanently retained thereafter, internal lighting in the cricket lanes playing area in accordance with the documents provided, with average lux >1000 taking into consideration netting, UGR < 19, Uniformity > 0.8, Reflectance at 0.7.

Reason: To safeguard the amenities of residents in accordance with the recommendations of the Institution of Lighting Professionals in the 'Guidance Note 01/20 For the Reduction of Obtrusive Light', Policies D6 and D5 of the London Plan (2021) and Policy 7A of Ealing's Development Management DPD (2013). | The demolition method statement/ construction management plan prepared by Collinson Construction shall be implemented prior and during the commencement of the proposed development.

Reason: In the interests of the amenity of adjoining occupiers and to minimise highway and traffic impact during the course of the works, in accordance with 1.1 (e) (j) 1.2 (f), 2.1 (c) and 2.10 of the Ealing Core Strategy (2012), policies D6, D14 and T7 of the London Plan (2021), the National Planning Policy Framework (2021), Greater London Authority Best Practice Guidance 'The Control of Dust and Emissions from Construction and Demolition (2006), BS 5228-1:2009 - Code of practice for noise & vibration control on construction & open sites-Part 1: Noise density. | The Tree Protection Plan, shall be in accordance with the approved details of application ref: 211743CND dated 03.03.2021.

Reason: To ensure appropriate tree protection in the interests of protecting the visual amenity of the area, contributing to the quality and character of London's environment, air quality and adapting to and mitigating climate change in accordance with policies SI1 and G7 of the London Plan (2021), policy 5.10 of Ealing's Development Management DPD (2013) and Ealing's SPG 9 - Trees and Development Guidelines. | Cycle storage for twelve (12) bicycle spaces shall be provided within the curtilage of the site, within a secure, lockable compound in accordance with all adopted standards prior to occupation of the building and be continuously available and retained for the life of the development hereby approved.

Reason: To provide adequate bicycle storage to align with Sustainable Transport SPG and T5 of the London Plan (2021). | The development hereby approved shall not be occupied until refuse and recycling storage within an enclosure has been provided, as per the approved site plan and design and access statement, in accordance with the Local Planning Authority Standards and has been fully implemented and made available for use. These facilities shall thereafter be retained for use at all times.

Reason: To ensure the provision of satisfactory facilities for the storage of refuse and recycling material, in accordance with policies 1.1 and 1.2 of the Adopted Ealing Development (Core) Strategy (2012) policy 7B of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013) and policies SI7 and SI8 of the London Plan (2021). | The agronomist assessment and specification of works for the relocated cricket wicket square, shall be in accordance with the approved details of application ref: 211744CND dated 28.05.2021.

Reason: To ensure that the cricket wicket is prepared to an adequate standard and is fit for purpose and to accord with Policy S5 of the London Plan (2021) and Policy 7D of the Ealing Development Management Plan (2013). | The continuity of the existing sports use for existing users shall be ensured in accordance with the approved details of application ref: 211600CND dated 28.05.2021.

Reason: To ensure the satisfactory accessibility of provision which secures a continuity of use and to accord with Policy S5 of the London Plan (2021) and Policy 7D of the Ealing Development Management Plan (2013). | Use of the development shall not commence until a community use agreement prepared in consultation with Sport England has been submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority, and a copy of the completed approved agreement has been provided to the Local Planning Authority.  The agreement shall apply to at least the building except for the first floor fitness suite and Multi use Area hereby permitted and relocated cricket wicket and include details of pricing policy, hours of use, access by non- non-members, management responsibilities and a mechanism for review.  The development shall not be used otherwise than in strict compliance with the approved agreement.

Reason: To secure well managed safe community access to the sports facility/facilities, to ensure sufficient benefit to the development of sport and accord with Policies S1 and S5 of the London Plan (2021) and Policy 7D of the Ealing Development Management Plan (2013). | The construction details of the specifications, design and layout of the proposed heat pumps and PV equipment and associated monitoring devices required to identify their performance/efficiency (COP) shall be in accordance with the approved details of application ref: 211745CND dated 18.02.2021 and Energy Statement Report Addendum prepared by Pettit Singleton Associates dated October 2021.

Reason: In the interest of addressing climate change and to secure environmental sustainable development in accordance with policies SI1, SI2 and SI3 of the London Plan 2021, guidance note 11 of the GLA Energy Assessment Guidance 2018, policies LV5.2 and 7A of Ealing's Development Management DPD 2013, and policies 1.1(k) and 1.2(f) of Ealing's Development (Core) Strategy 2012. | In order to implement Ealing Council DPD policy 5.2.3 (post-construction energy monitoring), and the London Plan policy SI2 with the "Be Seen" stage of the revised energy hierarchy, the developer shall:

a)	Upon final construction suitable devices for monitoring the performance/efficiency (COP) of any renewable/low-carbon energy equipment shall be installed. The monitored data shall be automatically submitted to the Council at daily intervals for a period of four years from occupation and full operation of the energy equipment. The installation of the monitoring devices and the submission and format of the data shall be carried out in accordance with the Council's approved specifications as indicated in the Automated Energy Monitoring Platform (AEMP) information document. The developer must contact the Council's chosen AEMP supplier (Energence Ltd) on commencement of construction to facilitate the monitoring process.

b)	Upon final completion of the development and prior to occupation, the developer must submit to the Council proof of a contractual arrangement with a certified contractor that provides for the ongoing, commissioning, maintenance, and repair of the renewable/low-carbon energy equipment for a period of three years from the point that the building is occupied and the equipment fully operational.

Reason: To monitor the effectiveness and continued operation of the renewable/low carbon energy equipment in order to confirm compliance with energy policies and establish an in-situ evidence base on the performance of such equipment in accordance with London Plan policy Si2 ("Be Seen" stage of the energy hierarchy), Ealing's Development (Core) Strategy 2026 (3rd April 2012) and Development Management DPD policy 5.2, E5.2.3, and Policy 2.5.36 (Best Practice) of the Mayor's Sustainable Design & Construction SPG. | Use of the first floor fitness suite and Multi-use Area hereby permitted development shall not commence until a Community Use Agreement prepared in consultation with Sport England has been submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority, and a copy of the completed approved agreement has been provided to the Local Planning Authority.  The agreement shall apply to at least the first floor fitness suite and Multi-use Area hereby permitted and include details of pricing policy, hours of use, access by non- non-members, management responsibilities and a mechanism for review.  The development shall not be used otherwise than in strict compliance with the approved agreement.

Reason: To secure well managed safe community access to the sports facility/facilities, to ensure sufficient benefit to the development of sport and accord with Policies S1 and S5 of the London Plan (2021) and Policy 7D of the Ealing Development Management Plan (2013).
description: Minor material amendment (S.73) to vary condition no.2 (approved plans), seeking to allow changes to the design, in pursuant to planning permission reference 203084FUL dated 21/12/2020 for 'Construction of a sport pavilion'
